WEBVTT

00:00.542 --> 00:02.877
- Previously on
"Superman & Lois"...

00:02.919 --> 00:06.464
- Setting him free would be the
biggest mistake of your life.

00:06.506 --> 00:08.299
- He threatened me,
told me to retire

00:08.341 --> 00:10.010
from journalism,
or he would come back.

00:10.051 --> 00:12.512
- He'd have to go through me
and Superman to hurt you.

00:12.554 --> 00:13.805
And that's not gonna happen.

00:13.847 --> 00:15.390
- Something I can do for you?

00:15.432 --> 00:17.684
- Every time you die,
it just makes you stronger.

00:17.726 --> 00:22.772
Let me kill you so nothing
in this world can stop you--

00:22.814 --> 00:24.399
nothing.

00:24.441 --> 00:27.694
Ever think about dying,
Superman?

00:27.736 --> 00:29.529
Because you're about to.

00:33.908 --> 00:36.536
- [roaring]

00:36.578 --> 00:38.163
- What's he done to you?

00:38.204 --> 00:41.499
[dramatic music]

00:41.541 --> 00:45.837
- When you're done,
bring me his heart.

00:52.802 --> 00:53.762
- Don't.

00:53.803 --> 01:00.643
♪ ♪

01:02.020 --> 01:03.813
- [roaring]

01:21.748 --> 01:23.124
- What's happening?

01:23.166 --> 01:26.044
- I can't hear him
breathing anymore.

01:42.519 --> 01:45.105
- [snarling]

01:47.440 --> 01:50.527
[snarling]

02:00.829 --> 02:03.790
[roaring]

02:03.832 --> 02:10.922
♪ ♪

03:38.843 --> 03:40.803
- That thing was at our house.

03:40.845 --> 03:43.139
How did it know to come here?

03:43.181 --> 03:44.724
- I don't know.

03:44.766 --> 03:46.142
[whoosh]

03:46.184 --> 03:47.894
- I found this not far
from the barn.

03:47.936 --> 03:50.313
- Grandpa's ELT.

03:50.355 --> 03:52.023
- After he went missing,
your dad must have

03:52.065 --> 03:53.191
come here looking for him.

03:53.233 --> 03:54.234
- You think Granddad was here?

03:54.275 --> 03:55.777
- No, but Luthor was.

03:55.818 --> 03:58.071
And my guess is he used
that to call his new pet.

03:58.112 --> 04:01.658
- So that's why he wanted
Granddad, to get the ELT.

04:03.159 --> 04:07.330
- It's easy to be brave
with Superman and the DOD

04:07.372 --> 04:08.957
watching out for you.

04:11.501 --> 04:13.836
- I need you to listen for
your grandfather's voice.

04:13.878 --> 04:15.296
- Why not Dad?
- You heard what he said.

04:15.338 --> 04:17.048
He didn't want any of us
to engage.

04:17.090 --> 04:18.549
Just concentrate on
your grandfather.

04:18.591 --> 04:19.968
We have to find him now.

04:21.261 --> 04:23.179
[high-pitched warbling]

04:23.221 --> 04:25.139
[discordant noises]

04:25.181 --> 04:28.142
[suspenseful music]

04:28.184 --> 04:32.897
♪ ♪

04:32.939 --> 04:35.900
[rock music]

04:35.942 --> 04:43.032
♪ ♪

04:48.997 --> 04:51.499
- Really?

04:51.541 --> 04:53.001
- Hotel mine?

04:53.042 --> 04:54.544
- I purchased it through
Eckworth Industries

04:54.585 --> 04:56.629
to avoid any questions.

04:56.671 --> 04:57.630
You overpaid.

04:57.672 --> 04:59.340
- No, I didn't.

04:59.382 --> 05:02.176
- It's been over a month since
you've been out of prison.

05:02.218 --> 05:04.387
Why haven't you been back
to LuthorCorp yet?

05:04.429 --> 05:06.306
- I have things to do here.

05:06.347 --> 05:08.683
- And how much longer do you
expect these things will take?

05:08.725 --> 05:09.976
The board is getting restless.

05:10.018 --> 05:11.602
- Not my concern.

05:11.644 --> 05:14.689
- They're all spineless
sycophants, especially Bash.

05:14.731 --> 05:16.357
Anything I can tell
them about how you want

05:16.399 --> 05:18.151
things to run moving forward?

05:18.192 --> 05:20.236
- Nothing changes.

05:20.278 --> 05:22.989
Everything's been operating as
it should be the last 17 years.

05:23.031 --> 05:26.492
- I'm pretty sure they're sick
of getting orders from me.

05:26.534 --> 05:29.370
- Which tells me
you're doing it right.

05:29.412 --> 05:33.207
[suspenseful music]

05:33.249 --> 05:36.711
There's a reason you're
the only one I trust.

05:38.755 --> 05:40.673
- Consider it handled.

05:43.259 --> 05:45.094
- Any word on Elizabeth?

05:47.221 --> 05:50.308
- She left London before
you were released.

05:54.520 --> 05:57.774
- Keep looking.

05:57.815 --> 05:59.776
She can't just disappear.

06:01.819 --> 06:03.988
- Can I please fix
this place up for you?

06:04.030 --> 06:05.865
- This is everything I need.

06:05.907 --> 06:07.617
- At least let me get you
some window dressings.

06:07.658 --> 06:11.662
- Amanda,
it's not a prison cell.

06:13.748 --> 06:15.416
That's enough for me.

06:15.458 --> 06:22.507
♪ ♪

06:26.094 --> 06:30.056
But there is one thing
I need Milton to build.

06:34.644 --> 06:36.604
[car doors slam]

06:36.646 --> 06:37.730
- [groans]

06:37.772 --> 06:39.023
- I'll get him.

06:39.065 --> 06:41.067
- I'm sure as hell
not gonna do it.

06:42.610 --> 06:45.696
- [groaning]

07:01.504 --> 07:03.589
- Date's not over yet.

07:03.631 --> 07:05.007
[muffled speech]

07:05.049 --> 07:07.802
[high-pitched warbling]

07:11.973 --> 07:14.684
- It's all, like,
muffled or something.

07:14.725 --> 07:16.352
- You think it's Grandpa?

07:16.394 --> 07:18.229
[muffled speech]

07:18.271 --> 07:19.772
- I don't know.

07:19.814 --> 07:21.524
Maybe.

07:21.566 --> 07:25.528
- I know this is hard, sweetie,
but you have to keep trying.

07:25.570 --> 07:26.946
Help him.

07:29.031 --> 07:31.242
- Where are you going?
- To think.

07:31.284 --> 07:34.036
The radiation makes
my brain foggy.

07:34.078 --> 07:37.165
[heart beating]

07:39.959 --> 07:41.335
- How can you do that?

07:41.377 --> 07:44.338
Your heartbeat,
like, never rises.

07:46.174 --> 07:50.845
- I just try not
to give in to the fear.

07:50.887 --> 07:53.848
Just sort of how
I'm built, I guess.

07:53.890 --> 07:56.601
[soft apprehensive music]

07:56.642 --> 08:02.315
- That thing Dad was fighting,
how could he beat that?

08:02.356 --> 08:04.442
- He'll beat it.

08:04.484 --> 08:06.819
- Did you see the look
on his face?

08:09.780 --> 08:12.950
Dad was scared.

08:12.992 --> 08:15.036
What if he knew
he couldn't beat it?

08:15.077 --> 08:17.455
- He will.

08:17.497 --> 08:19.123
We have to believe that.

08:19.165 --> 08:20.875
- I don't know if I do.

08:22.502 --> 08:23.711
Not this time.

08:25.213 --> 08:29.050
And without Dad, man,
I'm just not ready

08:29.091 --> 08:31.177
to do all this without him.

08:31.219 --> 08:38.309
♪ ♪

08:58.496 --> 08:59.914
- You okay?

09:09.173 --> 09:13.219
Maybe a glass of wine?

09:13.261 --> 09:14.554
Something stronger.

09:14.595 --> 09:18.307
- I just have
so many questions.

09:18.349 --> 09:19.976
- I know. I know.

09:20.017 --> 09:21.519
And my mom thought you could
probably use some space,

09:21.561 --> 09:23.980
so she went into town
to give us some privacy.

09:24.021 --> 09:27.650
So I'll answer any
questions you have.

09:29.402 --> 09:30.945
- Why tell me now?

09:32.697 --> 09:35.116
- Because I'm in love with you,

09:35.157 --> 09:38.869
more in love than I
ever thought I could be.

09:38.911 --> 09:41.080
- So when you
heard me tell Janet

09:41.122 --> 09:44.500
that I was in love during
the Superman interview...

09:44.542 --> 09:48.713
- That was the best day
of my life.

09:48.754 --> 09:50.923
- Even if I called you dorky?

09:50.965 --> 09:53.593
- Sometimes,
I'm a little dorky.

09:53.634 --> 09:57.179
[soft music]

09:57.221 --> 09:59.056
You're mad?

10:10.109 --> 10:12.069
Mm, definitely not mad.

10:12.111 --> 10:13.738
Oh, oh, um, you wanna--

10:13.779 --> 10:15.239
- Go to your bedroom,
right now.

10:15.281 --> 10:16.782
- Okay.

10:16.824 --> 10:17.992
- You said she wanted
to give us space, right?

10:18.034 --> 10:19.160
- Yeah, no,
she won't be back.

10:19.201 --> 10:23.122
It's just, um,
I've never, um...

10:23.164 --> 10:24.540
- Done it
in your childhood bedroom?

10:24.582 --> 10:27.168
It'll be fine.

10:27.209 --> 10:30.212
I'll turn the Cal Ripken
around so he's not watching!

10:30.254 --> 10:32.214
- That's not--
that's not what I meant.

10:32.256 --> 10:33.341
Um...

10:35.593 --> 10:37.553
I've never...

10:40.556 --> 10:41.807
- Oh.

10:46.646 --> 10:49.273
I love you.

10:49.315 --> 10:51.275
There's no one else for me.

10:53.653 --> 10:56.197
- I love you too.

10:56.238 --> 10:58.199
- Good.

10:58.240 --> 11:01.410
Then get ready to have
a new best day of your life.

11:03.579 --> 11:04.914
- Mm!

11:04.955 --> 11:12.046
♪ ♪

11:16.926 --> 11:19.679
[whirring]

11:23.849 --> 11:26.894
- Where are you, Clark?

11:26.936 --> 11:29.897
[voice echoing]

11:29.939 --> 11:32.900
[dramatic music]

11:32.942 --> 11:40.032
♪ ♪

11:45.329 --> 11:48.749
- [snarling]

12:16.068 --> 12:17.153
[snarls]

12:28.998 --> 12:31.751
[snarling]

12:36.714 --> 12:40.134
[roaring]

12:40.176 --> 12:44.180
♪ ♪

12:48.517 --> 12:51.479
[peaceful music]

12:51.520 --> 12:54.315
♪ ♪

12:54.356 --> 12:56.358
- Chrissy, have you
seen the case file on--

12:56.400 --> 12:57.443
- Not Chrissy.

12:57.485 --> 13:00.279
[soft tense music]

13:00.321 --> 13:04.116
♪ ♪

13:04.158 --> 13:05.826
- What have you done
with my father?

13:05.868 --> 13:08.579
- I walked to your house
and made you an offer.

13:08.621 --> 13:10.039
- You threatened me.

13:10.080 --> 13:12.166
- There was no threat
if you retired.

13:12.208 --> 13:14.251
But I was clear.

13:14.293 --> 13:16.253
You don't get to have
your words in print anymore,

13:16.295 --> 13:18.088
not after what you did.

13:18.130 --> 13:20.674
- You left this at my house
after you called that thing.

13:20.716 --> 13:21.842
- Did I?

13:24.303 --> 13:25.304
Prove it.

13:25.346 --> 13:27.807
- This isn't a game.

13:27.848 --> 13:30.226
- If you didn't want this,
you should have taken my offer.

13:30.267 --> 13:31.769
- Where's my dad?

13:31.811 --> 13:33.979
- He won't be
protecting you anymore.

13:34.021 --> 13:35.481
Neither will Superman.

13:35.523 --> 13:36.941
- I don't need protection.

13:36.982 --> 13:38.359
- You have been
hiding behind Superman

13:38.400 --> 13:40.653
and the general
your entire career.

13:42.363 --> 13:43.572
Those days are over.

13:43.614 --> 13:44.907
- You want me to retire?

13:44.949 --> 13:46.617
Fine.

13:46.659 --> 13:49.578
Okay, I retire.

13:49.620 --> 13:51.372
- [chuckles]
You're not even a good liar.

13:51.413 --> 13:53.749
- If you have hurt him,
I swear to God,

13:53.791 --> 13:57.545
I will put you away for the
rest of your miserable life.

13:59.964 --> 14:02.174
- You like it here
in this small town?

14:03.759 --> 14:07.304
The "aw shucks"
and the apple pie?

14:10.349 --> 14:11.851
Makes you feel safe?

14:17.356 --> 14:19.400
Seems fake to me.

14:20.776 --> 14:24.405
Maybe being here
will change my mind.

14:24.446 --> 14:27.992
- So, what,
you're staying in Smallville?

14:29.243 --> 14:32.621
- Right there,
across the street.

14:32.663 --> 14:36.083
Oh, it's got the perfect view.

14:36.125 --> 14:38.335
- I'm not scared of you.

14:38.377 --> 14:41.714
- You will be.

14:41.755 --> 14:44.258
Being alone
like I was in prison,

14:44.300 --> 14:48.262
nearly losing the business
I built,

14:48.304 --> 14:53.225
having my daughter turn on me,

14:53.267 --> 14:56.937
it tested me in ways
you can't possibly imagine.

14:59.523 --> 15:01.734
At least not yet.

15:01.775 --> 15:08.324
♪ ♪

15:11.201 --> 15:13.287
Nice headline.

15:17.750 --> 15:19.460
- No one has seen
or heard from Superman

15:19.501 --> 15:21.086
since the attack took place.

15:21.128 --> 15:22.755
People have been gathering
here ever since,

15:22.796 --> 15:24.840
looking for any sign
of the Man of Steel.

15:24.882 --> 15:27.051
There are unconfirmed reports
that the assailants

15:27.092 --> 15:29.094
were using
Kryptonite weaponry.

15:29.136 --> 15:31.472
Police are continuing to
investigate the crime scene.

15:31.513 --> 15:34.099
- I can confirm those reports.

15:34.141 --> 15:35.225
- What happened?

15:35.267 --> 15:36.435
- Luthor.

15:36.477 --> 15:37.937
- He was there?

15:37.978 --> 15:40.189
- Eh, more Intergang,
maybe some yakuza.

15:40.230 --> 15:41.982
But the weapons were
definitely Luthor.

15:42.024 --> 15:43.734
- You're cut.

15:43.776 --> 15:47.279
- Huh? Oh.

15:47.321 --> 15:49.657
How do these guys keep
getting Kryptonite?

15:49.698 --> 15:50.950
- Let me get you a Band-Aid.

15:50.991 --> 15:52.576
- No, it's okay.
It'll just, um--

15:54.578 --> 15:55.663
Yeah.

15:57.831 --> 15:59.583
- You really had me
worried there.

15:59.625 --> 16:01.794
We just got married.
I'm not ready to be a widow.

16:01.835 --> 16:03.963
- That is never
gonna happen.

16:04.004 --> 16:05.464
- Says the guy who
was just attacked

16:05.506 --> 16:07.174
by two gangs with Kryptonite.

16:07.216 --> 16:08.634
- Yeah, and my cut healed.

16:08.676 --> 16:10.010
Plus, I can fly.

16:10.052 --> 16:11.011
I have heat vision...

16:11.053 --> 16:12.596
- Laser eyes.

16:12.638 --> 16:13.973
- And super strength,
not that I'm bragging.

16:14.014 --> 16:15.599
- You're totally bragging.

16:15.641 --> 16:18.727
- Hey, I just
don't want you to worry.

16:18.769 --> 16:20.354
- Kind of goes
with being in love.

16:20.396 --> 16:22.564
You worry.

16:22.606 --> 16:24.692
- I'm not going anywhere.

16:24.733 --> 16:27.653
You're stuck with me forever.

16:27.695 --> 16:29.780
- Promise?

16:29.822 --> 16:32.783
[soft music]

16:32.825 --> 16:34.493
♪ ♪

16:34.535 --> 16:37.496
[tense music]

16:37.538 --> 16:42.793
♪ ♪

16:42.835 --> 16:44.545
- I brought you
something to drink.

16:47.172 --> 16:48.716
- Go to hell.

16:48.757 --> 16:50.175
- Don't be like that.

16:52.344 --> 16:55.139
You need water.

16:55.180 --> 16:56.932
Fine.

16:56.974 --> 16:58.642
Suit yourself.

17:01.270 --> 17:03.731
- What do you want?

17:03.772 --> 17:06.525
The DOD doesn't negotiate
with people like you,

17:06.567 --> 17:09.695
so whatever you're looking for,
you're not gonna get it.

17:12.281 --> 17:14.283
- I'm pretty sure we will.

17:14.324 --> 17:17.161
- What kind of a person
does something like this?

17:17.202 --> 17:18.579
- How many people
have you kidnapped?

17:18.620 --> 17:21.498
Has to be in the hundreds,
at least.

17:21.540 --> 17:25.210
- That's not what
I was talking about.

17:25.252 --> 17:27.546
- You mean us?

17:27.588 --> 17:29.381
- Is any of it real?

17:29.423 --> 17:32.092
- My name's not Gretchen.

17:33.927 --> 17:36.722
But I did have a good time.

17:36.764 --> 17:39.975
- You were very convincing.

17:40.017 --> 17:41.060
- Thank you.

17:41.101 --> 17:42.811
- That wasn't a compliment.

17:44.521 --> 17:48.442
- No, I guess it wasn't.

17:51.070 --> 17:53.655
Can I ask you something?

17:53.697 --> 17:55.949
- I don't see where
I have much of a choice.

17:55.991 --> 17:59.078
- Had it really been that long
since you'd been with someone?

17:59.119 --> 18:05.667
♪ ♪

18:05.709 --> 18:07.628
I'm glad I could give you that.

18:07.669 --> 18:09.546
- You're a disgrace.

18:09.588 --> 18:12.591
- I've been called worse
by better.

18:12.633 --> 18:13.801
- We done here?

18:13.842 --> 18:16.762
- Yeah.

18:16.804 --> 18:18.847
I think so.

18:20.766 --> 18:24.728
[high-pitched warbling]

18:24.770 --> 18:28.273
[garbled voices]

18:30.025 --> 18:32.069
- Come on. Let's go eat.
I'm starving.

18:32.111 --> 18:33.821
- I still can't hear Granddad.

18:33.862 --> 18:36.365
- That doesn't mean
he's dead, okay?

18:36.406 --> 18:38.325
Maybe you just need
something to eat

18:38.367 --> 18:40.202
to help you, like, hone in.

18:40.244 --> 18:42.037
- The only reason he went out
with her was because of me.

18:42.079 --> 18:44.456
Jordan, I'm the one
who showed him the app,

18:44.498 --> 18:46.959
told him to get out there.

18:47.000 --> 18:48.877
And if that lady kills him--

18:48.919 --> 18:50.337
- She's not going to kill him.

18:50.379 --> 18:51.755
- You don't know that!

18:51.797 --> 18:53.090
For all we know,
he's dead already,

18:53.132 --> 18:54.258
and if he is, it's my fault.

18:54.299 --> 18:56.051
- Dude, stop, okay?

18:56.093 --> 18:58.220
All you were trying to do
was help Grandpa.

18:58.262 --> 19:00.264
And it worked, okay?
He was crazy happy.

19:00.305 --> 19:02.975
It was like watching a body
snatcher movie or something.

19:03.016 --> 19:05.853
It is not your fault
that Lex Luthor

19:05.894 --> 19:07.604
had some month-long plan
to kidnap him.

19:07.646 --> 19:12.025
But if you keep blaming
yourself, Grandpa might die.

19:12.067 --> 19:14.862
That's the truth.

19:14.903 --> 19:17.573
So please stop.

19:17.614 --> 19:19.283
[soft apprehensive music]

19:19.324 --> 19:20.742
- Yeah.

19:20.784 --> 19:21.785
Okay.

19:21.827 --> 19:23.078
You're right.

19:23.120 --> 19:24.663
- I know.

19:26.206 --> 19:27.583
Now, let's go eat.

19:30.627 --> 19:34.006
[phone buzzing]

19:34.047 --> 19:37.009
[soft tense music]

19:37.050 --> 19:39.469
♪ ♪

19:39.511 --> 19:40.721
- He with you?

19:43.640 --> 19:44.892
- Yeah.

19:46.560 --> 19:48.687
Anything change
with the daughter?

19:48.729 --> 19:51.064
- Just more lies.

19:51.106 --> 19:53.567
- Copy that.

19:53.609 --> 19:55.944
- One to the head,
one to the heart.

19:55.986 --> 19:58.030
Have Otis clean up after.

19:58.071 --> 20:01.825
♪ ♪

20:06.496 --> 20:09.166
- That was Lex Luthor,
wasn't it?

20:09.208 --> 20:10.792
You work for him?

20:12.669 --> 20:15.547
Look, I have
three grandchildren.

20:15.589 --> 20:17.132
You met them.

20:17.174 --> 20:18.926
They're amazing kids.

20:18.967 --> 20:21.595
My granddaughter, she only
recently came into my life.

20:21.637 --> 20:23.639
We're just getting
to know each other.

20:23.680 --> 20:25.349
She's lost a lot
of people already.

20:25.390 --> 20:28.018
I don't think she can
handle another one.

20:28.060 --> 20:31.647
Whatever Luthor has on you,
I can get you away from him,

20:31.688 --> 20:33.732
put you anywhere you want,

20:33.774 --> 20:36.276
give you a new name,
a new life.

20:36.318 --> 20:38.612
I can protect you.

20:38.654 --> 20:41.615
[soft tense music]

20:41.657 --> 20:48.747
♪ ♪

20:53.877 --> 20:56.421
- I wish that were true.

20:59.549 --> 21:02.427
But no one can hide
from Luthor.

21:07.224 --> 21:08.767
You're a good man.

21:10.477 --> 21:12.938
I'm sorry it had
to happen like this.

21:12.980 --> 21:20.070
♪ ♪

21:20.654 --> 21:24.950
- Why don't you try and fly up
into the atmosphere this time?

21:24.992 --> 21:27.411
Might get better reception
up there.

21:27.452 --> 21:30.289
- Go get the check.

21:30.330 --> 21:31.915
[bells tinkle]

21:33.583 --> 21:35.377
What's wrong?

21:39.506 --> 21:42.759
[ominous music]

21:42.801 --> 21:49.891
♪ ♪

21:55.355 --> 21:57.816
- I take it you know who I am.

21:57.858 --> 21:59.943
Your mother told you
why I'm here?

21:59.985 --> 22:01.737
- We know why you're here.

22:01.778 --> 22:05.032
- 'Cause you're
a straight-up psycho.

22:05.073 --> 22:06.450
- Ah.

22:10.954 --> 22:16.126
17 years ago, your mother
and her good friend Superman

22:16.168 --> 22:19.338
put me in prison
for crimes I didn't commit.

22:23.592 --> 22:28.597
This is my daughter, Elizabeth.

22:28.638 --> 22:31.516
This is what she looked like
the last time I saw her,

22:31.558 --> 22:32.976
dropping her off to school.

22:33.018 --> 22:35.437
She meant everything to me.

22:35.479 --> 22:38.732
Elizabeth was the only person
in my life that loved me.

22:38.774 --> 22:41.943
Not my mother,
not my ex-wife...

22:44.863 --> 22:46.156
Just her.

22:47.324 --> 22:49.785
- Kind of sounds like
you're the problem.

22:49.826 --> 22:51.286
[table rattles]

22:54.748 --> 22:57.584
- Boys, everything okay?

22:57.626 --> 23:04.716
♪ ♪

23:08.095 --> 23:12.140
- Your mother took her from me.

23:14.059 --> 23:19.439
Everything that's coming
is justified.

23:19.481 --> 23:26.571
♪ ♪

23:33.662 --> 23:36.206
What the hell
are you doing, Lois?

23:36.248 --> 23:38.458
You can't print this story.

23:38.500 --> 23:39.960
- Presses are already running.

23:40.001 --> 23:42.462
- I told you
that voice wasn't me.

23:42.504 --> 23:45.590
- Well, the recording
suggests otherwise.

23:45.632 --> 23:48.635
- Do not run that story.

23:48.677 --> 23:51.847
- This is not some
criminal enterprise of yours.

23:51.888 --> 23:53.432
This is the "Daily Planet."

23:53.473 --> 23:54.766
- Then I'll buy
the "Daily Planet"!

23:54.808 --> 23:56.143
- From prison?

23:56.184 --> 23:58.520
Not likely.

23:58.562 --> 24:02.107
- This makes you feel powerful,
doesn't it,

24:02.149 --> 24:03.525
deciding someone's fate?

24:03.567 --> 24:05.360
- I'm just reporting the truth.

24:05.402 --> 24:08.029
- No, you're doing real harm.

24:08.071 --> 24:11.324
- That is rich coming from you.

24:13.160 --> 24:16.663
- This crusade against me,

24:16.705 --> 24:19.166
it isn't about Moxie
or Intergang.

24:19.207 --> 24:21.126
It's about your friend.

24:21.168 --> 24:22.836
You're trying to protect him.

24:22.878 --> 24:25.088
- Superman doesn't
need my protection.

24:25.130 --> 24:27.215
- No, no, you have been
after me

24:27.257 --> 24:29.468
ever since I discovered
his weakness.

24:29.509 --> 24:31.052
- That has nothing
to do with this.

24:31.094 --> 24:33.180
- There's more Kryptonite
out there, Lois.

24:33.221 --> 24:36.057
Don't make me expose it
to the world.

24:37.851 --> 24:40.520
- Get the hell
out of my office.

24:40.562 --> 24:43.523
[tense music]

24:43.565 --> 24:48.195
♪ ♪

24:48.236 --> 24:49.905
[door closes]

24:49.946 --> 24:51.907
- Lex Luthor is here.
- We saw him at Vicky May's.

24:51.948 --> 24:53.366
- Where he pretty much admitted
being behind

24:53.408 --> 24:54.784
everything that's happening.

24:54.826 --> 24:56.870
- I know.
He came in here earlier.

24:56.912 --> 24:58.705
- Well, we have to
do something.

24:58.747 --> 25:00.790
- We can't, honey.

25:00.832 --> 25:02.083
- I can.

25:02.125 --> 25:04.002
- Jordan, you stay away
from him.

25:04.044 --> 25:05.128
- He just walked
into the hotel.

25:05.170 --> 25:06.588
No one else is even in there.

25:06.630 --> 25:08.298
- Jordan, I said no.
Do you understand?

25:08.340 --> 25:10.175
- Mom, maybe Jordan's right.

25:10.217 --> 25:12.385
- I have known Lex Luthor
long enough to know

25:12.427 --> 25:13.845
that this is just
the beginning.

25:13.887 --> 25:16.598
You stay away from him,
both of you.

25:16.640 --> 25:18.934
Please, just focus on
finding your grandfather.

25:18.975 --> 25:20.143
He needs our help.

25:20.185 --> 25:22.854
[suspenseful music]

25:22.896 --> 25:29.986
♪ ♪

25:55.512 --> 25:59.808
[shovel clattering]

25:59.849 --> 26:03.311
- Pretty pathetic,
hitting a woman,

26:03.353 --> 26:04.938
even if she was
supposed to kill you.

26:04.980 --> 26:06.815
- Shut up, Otis.

26:06.856 --> 26:08.316
- Probably the reason
he was on that loser app

26:08.358 --> 26:09.359
in the first place.

26:09.401 --> 26:10.527
- That's enough.

26:10.569 --> 26:12.195
[suspenseful music]

26:12.237 --> 26:13.363
- Lex.

26:13.405 --> 26:15.282
- We can discuss this later.

26:16.950 --> 26:19.786
- [groaning]

26:21.788 --> 26:25.250
I was going to
make this painless,

26:25.292 --> 26:27.794
but then you decided
to try to escape.

26:27.836 --> 26:32.215
- Didn't peg you as one
to twist the knife.

26:32.257 --> 26:34.175
Guess I gave you
too much credit.

26:34.217 --> 26:37.137
- I thought you might wanna
look at your daughter's paper,

26:37.178 --> 26:40.098
seeing as it's the reason
you're here.

26:40.140 --> 26:41.891
- Lois isn't to blame for this.

26:41.933 --> 26:43.518
- She made her choice.

26:43.560 --> 26:46.813
Looking after you just
wasn't a top priority.

26:46.855 --> 26:49.065
- Wanna lecture me
about daughters?

26:49.107 --> 26:50.900
At least mine
still talked to me.

26:50.942 --> 26:53.278
How's Elizabeth doing anyway?

26:53.320 --> 26:54.487
Do you know where she is?
- Enough.

26:54.529 --> 26:57.449
- Who she is?
- Enough!

26:58.992 --> 27:02.495
No one is coming
to save you, General.

27:02.537 --> 27:04.748
See for yourself.

27:07.083 --> 27:09.002
- He always comes back.

27:09.044 --> 27:11.171
- Not this time.

27:13.590 --> 27:15.634
- [groans]

27:15.675 --> 27:18.178
Keep the sand wet.

27:18.219 --> 27:20.430
It'll make his choking
more painful.

27:20.472 --> 27:27.562
♪ ♪

27:37.822 --> 27:40.909
- [groaning]

27:45.121 --> 27:47.165
- Ms. Lane,
listen to my voice.

27:47.207 --> 27:48.750
- What's happening?

27:48.792 --> 27:50.669
- I'm right here.

27:50.710 --> 27:53.171
Everything's gonna be okay.
You just had a small seizure.

27:53.213 --> 27:55.423
- Okay, is that normal?
- I need to get Dr. Patel.

27:55.465 --> 27:56.758
She'll explain everything.

27:56.800 --> 27:58.843
- [moaning]

27:58.885 --> 28:00.512
- I'm taking you
to the fortress.

28:00.553 --> 28:02.055
- Clark.

28:02.097 --> 28:03.431
- I'm worried
it may be eclampsia.

28:03.473 --> 28:04.683
- Something is wrong.

28:04.724 --> 28:06.017
- Dr. Patel will handle it.

28:06.059 --> 28:07.352
- We can't take that chance.

28:07.394 --> 28:08.937
- We talked about this.

28:08.978 --> 28:10.313
No Kryptonian tech.
- Things have changed.

28:10.355 --> 28:11.731
You just had a seizure.

28:11.773 --> 28:13.441
- I'm fine.
- Lois, I can't lose you.

28:13.483 --> 28:14.943
- Snap out of it, Clark!

28:14.984 --> 28:16.611
I understand that this is hard,

28:16.653 --> 28:18.571
but I am the one
who is giving birth.

28:18.613 --> 28:20.949
You don't get to freak out
just 'cause you're worried.

28:20.990 --> 28:22.742
We both worry about each other.

28:22.784 --> 28:23.952
- Yeah, but I can't--

28:23.993 --> 28:25.495
- Die?
- Yeah.

28:25.537 --> 28:27.789
- That doesn't keep me
from worrying about you.

28:27.831 --> 28:29.541
How many times
have I had to explain to you

28:29.582 --> 28:31.710
that worrying is just
a part of being in love?

28:31.751 --> 28:33.253
- Okay, okay, okay.
You're right.

28:33.294 --> 28:34.754
- Yes, I know I am right!

28:34.796 --> 28:36.381
Now, could you please
go get Dr. Patel

28:36.423 --> 28:38.550
so she can deliver
these babies?

28:38.591 --> 28:41.803
Oh, I am so over having twins!

28:41.845 --> 28:43.930
They're like
two little gremlins

28:43.972 --> 28:48.017
knocking against each other!

28:48.059 --> 28:49.436
- All right, all right.

28:49.477 --> 28:51.688
- No, no!
- I'm staying. I'm staying.

28:51.730 --> 28:53.231
I'm staying right here,
right here.

28:53.273 --> 28:54.691
- Okay.
- Okay, I'm right here.

28:54.733 --> 28:56.151
- [groaning]

28:56.192 --> 28:57.235
- Here they come.

28:57.277 --> 28:58.486
- Okay.

29:03.450 --> 29:04.701
- Mom.

29:04.743 --> 29:06.327
- What is it?
- It's Jordan.

29:06.369 --> 29:08.163
He thinks he heard
Grandpa screaming.

29:08.204 --> 29:11.541
[tense music]

29:11.583 --> 29:13.334
- Jordan.
- He stopped.

29:13.376 --> 29:14.711
- Try again.

29:14.753 --> 29:15.962
- I'm telling you,
there's nothing.

29:16.004 --> 29:18.590
It was really faint,
almost like he--

29:18.631 --> 29:20.258
- Was what? Whispering?

29:20.300 --> 29:22.802
- Had tape over his mouth?

29:22.844 --> 29:24.429
- More like he was choking.

29:24.471 --> 29:26.264
- Lex told me
he was gonna kill him.

29:26.306 --> 29:30.018
- Okay, Mom, we don't
know anything for sure.

29:30.059 --> 29:31.978
- Luthor always keeps his word.

29:33.396 --> 29:34.481
- Jordan?

29:34.522 --> 29:35.815
- He was trying so hard

29:35.857 --> 29:38.985
to be a good dad, and he was.

29:39.027 --> 29:40.987
I just never got a chance
to tell him that.

29:41.029 --> 29:42.739
- Let's get the hell
out of here.

29:42.781 --> 29:44.783
- Hold on.

29:44.824 --> 29:46.075
It's her.

29:46.117 --> 29:47.494
- Her?

29:47.535 --> 29:49.788
- That lady, the one
we saw with Granddad.

29:49.829 --> 29:51.915
His date.

29:51.956 --> 29:53.666
- Take me there.

29:55.627 --> 29:58.546
- I could use a warm shower
and a cold beer.

29:58.588 --> 30:00.173
Care to join?

30:00.215 --> 30:01.883
- Hard pass on both.

30:01.925 --> 30:04.385
[whoosh]

30:06.763 --> 30:08.640
- Where's my dad?

30:08.681 --> 30:11.226
- You're too late.

30:11.267 --> 30:14.521
- Kid looks like Snoopy
playing fighter pilot.

30:14.562 --> 30:17.440
[crunching, groaning]

30:21.986 --> 30:23.071
- I told you.

30:23.112 --> 30:24.489
- Where is he?

30:24.531 --> 30:27.867
- 50 yards that way.

30:27.909 --> 30:29.285
- They buried him!

30:32.330 --> 30:33.790
[whoosh]

30:33.832 --> 30:40.922
♪ ♪

30:47.220 --> 30:48.304
- [gasps]

30:50.223 --> 30:51.683
[coughing]

30:51.724 --> 30:53.685
- Grandpa.
Grandpa, are you okay?

30:55.854 --> 30:58.147
- Dad!

30:58.189 --> 31:03.319
♪ ♪

31:08.283 --> 31:10.368
- Second time
you've saved my life, kiddo.

31:10.410 --> 31:11.619
Thank you.

31:11.661 --> 31:13.246
- Those people
got away, though.

31:13.288 --> 31:15.081
- Not before you and your mom
roughed 'em up.

31:15.123 --> 31:16.249
Don't worry.

31:16.291 --> 31:18.418
They can't stay hidden
for long.

31:18.459 --> 31:20.628
- Yeah, what about Luthor?

31:20.670 --> 31:21.838
He's not hiding.

31:21.880 --> 31:23.131
- Don't worry about him
right now.

31:23.172 --> 31:25.008
We need to talk about Clark.

31:25.049 --> 31:28.678
[soft apprehensive music]

31:28.720 --> 31:30.471
- Boys, can you
give us a minute?

31:30.513 --> 31:37.604
♪ ♪

31:41.774 --> 31:44.903
- Before I was buried,

31:44.944 --> 31:49.240
Luthor showed me the headline
in today's "Gazette."

31:49.282 --> 31:51.701
What'd Luthor do, exactly?

31:54.704 --> 31:57.665
[tense music]

31:57.707 --> 32:04.797
♪ ♪

32:15.934 --> 32:18.102
- That's twice in one day.

32:18.144 --> 32:19.479
- Wasn't our fault this time.

32:19.520 --> 32:21.272
Lois Lane showed up
with that kid

32:21.314 --> 32:23.858
people have been
calling Superboy.

32:23.900 --> 32:25.526
- He's got powers?

32:25.568 --> 32:28.613
- He showed up in Smallville
about a month ago.

32:28.655 --> 32:35.620
♪ ♪

32:35.662 --> 32:36.913
- What's our next move?

32:36.955 --> 32:40.124
- Stay hidden until
you hear from me.

32:40.166 --> 32:42.293
Do not show your faces.

32:42.335 --> 32:44.170
- Where are you going?

32:45.922 --> 32:48.299
- To get what I asked for.

32:50.009 --> 32:51.844
- He must have planned
this whole thing

32:51.886 --> 32:53.763
the moment he was released
from prison.

32:53.805 --> 32:55.723
Once he got rid of you two,

32:55.765 --> 32:58.184
there'd be no one left
to protect me.

32:58.226 --> 33:00.478
Dad, he's coming after me.

33:02.814 --> 33:05.024
I know him. He won't stop.

33:05.066 --> 33:08.152
He wants to destroy my life
and everybody in it,

33:08.194 --> 33:12.573
turn the boys against me like
his daughter turned on him.

33:15.118 --> 33:17.662
And now with Clark gone--

33:17.704 --> 33:22.291
- Lois, that woman Gretchen--
whatever her name is--

33:22.333 --> 33:26.671
I let my guard down,
made myself an easy target.

33:26.713 --> 33:29.215
That won't happen again.

33:29.257 --> 33:30.717
And Clark?

33:30.758 --> 33:32.719
Well, they've tried
to kill him for years

33:32.760 --> 33:36.139
and failed every single time.

33:36.180 --> 33:39.392
You do not have to worry.

33:39.434 --> 33:41.519
- Dad, you don't understand.

33:41.561 --> 33:44.272
- Pumpkin, there's nothing
in this universe

33:44.313 --> 33:46.232
that can stop Superman.

33:48.359 --> 33:51.696
- There might be now.

33:51.738 --> 33:53.489
[dramatic music]

33:53.531 --> 33:56.159
- [snarling]

33:59.996 --> 34:01.414
[whoosh]

34:01.456 --> 34:08.546
♪ ♪

34:16.929 --> 34:18.806
[snarling]

34:29.817 --> 34:32.904
[high-pitched ringing]

34:49.629 --> 34:51.839
[snarling]

34:51.881 --> 34:58.971
♪ ♪

35:08.773 --> 35:11.317
[buzzing]

35:18.074 --> 35:21.035
[both shouting]

35:21.077 --> 35:28.167
♪ ♪

35:54.277 --> 35:56.487
- I think that nurse
is about ready to quit.

35:56.529 --> 35:58.114
- Yeah, well, how many times
did Granddad mention

35:58.156 --> 35:59.657
that he's a four-star general?

35:59.699 --> 36:01.117
- It was at least two.

36:01.159 --> 36:03.911
- All right, that's enough.

36:03.953 --> 36:07.623
[soft music]

36:07.665 --> 36:09.167
Come here.

36:14.172 --> 36:17.466
I love you both so much.

36:17.508 --> 36:18.509
- Love you, Mom.

36:18.551 --> 36:20.928
- Love you too.

36:20.970 --> 36:23.264
- And we are gonna get through
this like we always have--

36:23.306 --> 36:25.141
as a family.

36:25.183 --> 36:28.269
[high-pitched warbling]

36:30.438 --> 36:33.733
Jordan, what's wrong?

36:33.774 --> 36:35.943
[heart beating]

36:35.985 --> 36:38.529
- It's coming back.

36:38.571 --> 36:41.532
- [snarling softly]

36:41.574 --> 36:44.535
[tense music]

36:44.577 --> 36:51.667
♪ ♪

36:53.628 --> 36:56.172
- Good night, Chuck.
- Good night, Aidy.

36:56.214 --> 37:00.218
[whooshing]

37:04.597 --> 37:07.808
- [snarling]

37:07.850 --> 37:14.815
♪ ♪

37:14.857 --> 37:17.944
[snarling]

37:28.037 --> 37:29.455
- Oh, my God.

37:29.497 --> 37:32.500
- [snarling]

37:32.541 --> 37:39.632
♪ ♪

37:59.360 --> 38:00.820
- Not much to look at,

38:00.861 --> 38:02.947
but Milton assured me
it would work.

38:04.824 --> 38:06.325
- He did good.

38:06.367 --> 38:08.953
- How about we keep that
between us?

38:08.995 --> 38:11.956
Last thing that brainiac needs
is this going to his head.

38:13.457 --> 38:14.709
You need anything else?

38:14.750 --> 38:16.127
- No.

38:18.713 --> 38:20.548
- How about some company?

38:28.931 --> 38:32.226
I spent a lot of time
thinking about

38:32.268 --> 38:34.562
what it would it be like
once you got out of prison.

38:35.896 --> 38:37.064
- Me too.

38:38.816 --> 38:41.277
[whooshing]

38:41.319 --> 38:44.447
- [snarling]

38:44.488 --> 38:51.579
♪ ♪

39:07.887 --> 39:09.472
- Can't hear his heart beating.

39:17.229 --> 39:18.189
- [gasps]

39:18.230 --> 39:20.775
[sentimental music]

39:20.816 --> 39:23.361
♪ ♪

39:23.402 --> 39:28.282
I'm in love with someone else,
Clark from the paper.

39:28.324 --> 39:35.414
♪ ♪

40:27.174 --> 40:29.885
No, no, no, no.

40:29.927 --> 40:35.766
This wasn't supposed
to happen, not before me.

40:35.808 --> 40:38.018
No.

40:38.060 --> 40:39.603
- Mom, Dad.
- No.

40:39.645 --> 40:42.064
- Mom.
- No, boys.

40:42.106 --> 40:43.357
- Mom, is he okay?

40:43.399 --> 40:45.651
- [sobbing]
- Mom, is he okay?

40:45.693 --> 40:48.654
[somber music]

40:48.696 --> 40:55.786
♪ ♪

41:03.043 --> 41:05.921
- No, no.

41:05.963 --> 41:07.840
No!

41:07.882 --> 41:09.925
No.

41:14.263 --> 41:18.309
- [snarling]

41:18.350 --> 41:21.854
- Looks smaller in real life.

41:21.896 --> 41:23.898
- You have something for me?

41:23.939 --> 41:26.901
- [snarling]

41:26.942 --> 41:29.904
[tense music]

41:29.945 --> 41:32.323
♪ ♪

41:32.364 --> 41:34.492
Well done, friend.

41:34.533 --> 41:36.368
- [snarling]

41:36.410 --> 41:43.501
♪ ♪

42:02.144 --> 42:05.105
[dramatic music]

42:05.147 --> 42:12.238
♪ ♪

42:21.080 --> 42:23.123
- Greg, move your head.
